h3. Summary

When creating a board using a filter that includes '!=', for example : 
{code:java}
project = 'Scrum Project' AND epic link != 'epic party' {code}
All Epics that appear under *All Issues' in Backlog will disappear.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a Scrum Board with the filter :
{code:java}
project = 'Scrum Project' AND epic link != 'epic party' {code}
 # Head to the Backlog.

h3. Expected Results

All epics under *All Issues* will be listed out in the Backlog.
h3. Actual Results

No epics will appear under *All Issues* in the backlog.
h3. Workaround

Create a new filter with the below query and give it a name (e.g. Exclude DP-503)
{code:java}
Project = 'Not Equal' AND "Epic Link" = DP-503{code}
Run a search with the below query;
{code:java}
Project = 'Not Equal' and filter != 'Exclude DP-503'{code}
